entry.title: FREEZING RAIN WARNING, Killarney
entry.summary: Persons in or near this area should be on the lookout for adverse weather conditions and take necessary safety precautions. Issued: 10:52 p.m. EDT Tuesday 4 April 2023

entry.title: Tuesday night: Periods of freezing rain mixed with ice pellets. Low minus 1.
entry.summary: Periods of freezing rain mixed with ice pellets and risk of a thunderstorm. Snow and ice pellet amount 2 cm. Wind northeast 30 km/h gusting to 50. Low minus 1. Wind chill minus 8 overnight. Forecast issued 3:10 AM EDT Wednesday 5 April 2023

entry.title: Wednesday: Showers. High 7.
entry.summary: Periods of freezing rain changing to rain showers in the morning. Risk of a thunderstorm in the morning and afternoon. Rainfall amount 10 mm. Wind east 40 km/h gusting to 60 diminishing to 20 gusting to 40 late in the afternoon. High 7. UV index 2 or low. Forecast issued 3:10 AM EDT Wednesday 5 April 2023

entry.title: Wednesday night: Rain showers or flurries. Temperature rising to 11 in the evening then falling.
entry.summary: Rain showers ending before morning then cloudy with 30 percent chance of flurries. Rainfall amount 5 to 10 mm. Wind east 20 km/h gusting to 40 becoming light late in the evening. Wind becoming west 40 gusting to 70 near midnight. Temperature rising to 11 in the evening then falling. Forecast issued 3:10 AM EDT Wednesday 5 April 2023
